Setting up Tor with Proxychains is a foundational Operational Security (OpSec) technique used to anonymize network traffic by routing it through multiple nodes, making it extremely difficult to trace the original IP address.
 
What Tor and Proxychains Offer:

    Tor (The Onion Router): A decentralized network that encrypts traffic in multiple layers and routes it through at least three volunteer-run relays (nodes).
        Offers: IP masking, high anonymity, traffic analysis resistance, and access to .onion services.
    Proxychains: A tool that forces any TCP connection from an application to go through one or more proxy servers (HTTP, SOCKS4, SOCKS5, or Tor).
        Offers: Traffic redirection, multi-hop chaining (passing through several proxies), and the ability to use applications that don't support proxying by default. 

HOW TO SETUP:
 Setup on Linux (Debian / Ubuntu / Kali)
Proxychains is usually pre-installed on Kali. For Debian/Ubuntu, it is installed using proxychains4 (also known as Proxychains-NG). 
Step 1: Install Tor and Proxychains4 
```bash
# Update package lists and install Tor and Proxychains
sudo apt update
sudo apt install tor proxychains4 -y

Step 2: Start and Enable Tor Service 
```bash
# Start the Tor service
sudo service tor start

# Verify it is running
service tor status


Step 3: Configure Proxychains
Edit the configuration file. 
```bash
# Open the Proxychains configuration file for editing
sudo nano /etc/proxychains4.conf


    Uncomment dynamic_chain (removes the #): This ensures if one proxy fails, the chain continues.
    Comment out strict_chain: Strict requires all proxies to work; dynamic is more reliable.
    Uncomment proxy_dns: This is crucial to prevent DNS leaks.
    Add Tor to the list: At the end of the file, ensure the following is present (SOCKS5 is recommended):
    conf

```bash
# Add this line at the bottom of /etc/proxychains4.conf
socks5 127.0.0.1 9050


 

Step 4: Use it
Prefix any command with proxychains4. 
bash

```bash
# Launch Firefox through Proxychains to check for DNS leaks
proxychains4 firefox https://dnsleaktest.com

